race.comment: LEKTRA SOLO (2) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at this track over 450m behind Spring Coin (25.77) in a Grade 4/5. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. MIDNIGHT REBEL (1) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 25.68 beating Paw Pharah. Some good form is emerging from his last run. One of the key runners again. CRUISING JAMIE (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (25.59) at this track behind Spring Coin in a Grade 4/5. Has the pace to be prominent. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. INGA JOHNNY (7) can sneak into the finish with the right run.
